rComments: Unclear at times. Almost seems agitated while lecturing. Helpful when asked upon, and reasonably fair grader (she does some if not most on her own).

Utterly stellar professor. Entire course has fantastic structure and flow. Able to actively engage students in thought-provoking, discussion. Lectures are engaging, concise and informative. Easy to make connections between course factual material and real life legal cases. Incredibly reasonable expectations. Nothing but a positive experience!

The class is a complete joke, went to the first hour of the semester and she could possibly be the most boring prof I've ever had.  Reads off the slides and doesn't move. Have only done the assignments and haven't read anything, easy A if don't want to go to class and you can put a couple hours into each assignment.
She's a decent professor. I've had way worse, and she atleast has great slides that help in the assignments.

The assignments take time, not all that difficult. However, she is a little unclear in what she want you to do for them. On the other hand, her lectures are very structured and she has A LOT of slides per week.

I don't know what people are talking about. She is a very helpful professor the work is not easy but you can do very well if you do the readings. Anything that is unclear is more than happy to help you understand through the online discussions or in her office hours!
She is a bit confusing in her assignments but other that she is knowledgeable person and willing to help you out.
She is very quick to respond on class discussions. Not a push over for marks but its reflective to how much work you put in.
Her lecture slides are extensive making it very easy to follow along in class rather than dividing your attention to writing notes
She knows her stuff! the assignments are tedious but very doable.
She is a very knowledgeable prof and is more than helpful if you ask.

Worst Proff i've had in university, hands down. Never showed up to class, yet expected students to attend other sections of the class to 'catch up' on her missed classes. Expected perfection in assignments with no guidance. Missed 6 of the 12 weeks of classes. Avoid her at all costs.
How this lady is a prof is beyond my comprehension level. Still doesn't give out your mark and a  new semester has started. Absolutely horrible. Horible and AWFUL.

Intelligent - she knows her stuff and the mid term is very easy. Gives easy marks away for doing reading exercises every week that you only have to do 5/10 of for 10 % of your mark. Not only that, but those reading questions are topics on the final exam, so she's really gift wrapping marks. if you don't like to do the readings a D is possible

Not only is she useless as a prof,but she's also a really hard marker and expects nothing short of perfection from her students No explanation for why shes such a hard marker even though students have to teach themselves and she doesnt show up for some classes

Had her for small group torts. She`s clearly intelligent, but I had to start this listing to warn everyone to avoid taking a small group with her. She misses classes, does not often come prepared, deflects questions, and expects the class to do most of the work. Arbitrary marking scheme makes it frustrating for your first legal papers. AVOID!

This is the most useless prof I've had in my extended 5 year stay at Ottawa U.. I had to be the first to come on here and publicly out this woman who decided to skip 2 8:30 classes in a row in January on me.. she is late nearly half the classes and does not know how to teach, reads straight from her notes, stares off into space, and wastes my money
